Monday Bar Newsletter week 37 In this newsletter: MondayBar: The 2024 Cruise, September 20-22 • The cruise is fully booked (but check anyway..) • All floors and set times presented. • Don’t forget to bring a valid Passport or National ID • Make sure to complete your booking with all names! • Book your dinner, breakfast, brunch now and avoid waiting list • Board the ship from 16.00 (Swedish time). Pre-party on deck 10 • Bring your music box.. but not too big. Nothing that needs wheels… • Theme: Welcome to the Jungle - dress to impress! • "No 61” Cruise t-shirts and lanyards at C.U.M. Clubwear shop. Bring cash! Dear Monday Bar family, The cruise is sold out, but sometimes extra cabins are put out online so check the online site from time to time: https://se.tallink.com/monday-bar <https://se.tallink.com/monday-bar> There is also still a possibility that those of you who have booked a A, B or E cabin for only 2 people could upgrade to 3- or 4. Please call the booking office and find out if this is possible. Call 08-666 33 33 and have your booking reference ready. YOU NEED A VALID NATIONAL ID CARD or PASSPORT TO BOARD THE SHIP (Driver licence or regular ID card are not allowed) To get onboard, you need to prove your age and identity, but you also need to show what country you are from. It might be not possible to order a new ID or passport at this late stage, so if you don’t have this you can transfer the booking to someone else before the cruise. Call the booking office and have the booking reference available: +46 8 666 33 33 Valid identification are: - Passport - National ID card Not valid: - Regular ID card - Driver license Book your dinner now to avoid waiting list (cheaper) + make sure all passenger info is registered! Tallink-Silja has asked us to remind all to pre-book your meals (dinner, breakfast, brunch). That way you will be assured that you can have dinner at the best time for you. With this many people on board the restaurants will fill up quickly and there will be a waiting list if you haven't pre-booked. It’s also important that all persons staying in your cabin are registred! Please contact the booking department with your booking reference handy. There’s also a chat on the Tallink-Silja homepage. Tallink Silja booking office: +46 (0)8-666 33 33 info.sweden@tallinksilja.com <mailto:info.sweden@tallinksilja.com> You can also reserve tables online. Have your booking reference ready: In Swedish: https://se.tallink.com/hitta-resa <https://se.tallink.com/hitta-resa> In English: https://en.tallink.com/en/book-a-cruise <https://en.tallink.com/en/book-a-cruise> Restaurants onboard: Swedish: https://se.tallink.com/baltic-queen#tabs-content-3 <https://se.tallink.com/baltic-queen#tabs-content-3> English: https://en.tallink.com/en/baltic-queen-tallink-cruise-ship-stockholm-tallinn#tabs-content-2 <https://en.tallink.com/en/baltic-queen-tallink-cruise-ship-stockholm-tallinn#tabs-content-2> BOARD THE SHIP FROM 16.00 Boarding starts from 16.00. Last time to board is 17.10 and cruise then leaves at 17.30 sharp. But the party already starts at 16.00 at Disco Ibiza, deck 10. The sundeck next to the dance floor is also open with extra sound. IT’S FREE TO CHECK IN WITH THE MACHINES. But it costs 5 Euro to checkin manually at the checkin counters. Here’s info how to get to the ferry terminal (Tallink-Silja website). In Swedish: https://se.tallink.com/vartahamnen <https://se.tallink.com/vartahamnen> In English: https://en.tallink.com/stockholm-vartahamnen <https://en.tallink.com/stockholm-vartahamnen> PARKING CLOSE TO THE FERRY TERMINAL There’s a car park next to the ferry terminal. But make sure you are in good time since the traffic in Stockholm can be congested Friday afternoon. More parking info online: https://se.tallink.com/vartahamnen <https://se.tallink.com/vartahamnen> BRING YOUR OWN MUSIC MACHINE - BUT NOT TOO BIG It’s allowed to play music in the cabins, but not too loud so that it disturbs you, neighbours. No music is allowed between 06-10 in the morning. You can bring a music player, but not too big. Computer speakers, ”boom boxes” are ok, but anything that requires wheels to carry onboard will be confiscated when boarding. If it feels too big, it probably is.. And no music in the cabins between 06-10 so that we all can get some rest! CRUISE T-SHIRTS + MONDAY BAR LANYARDS - CASH ONLY There will be a limited number of t-shirts with the cruise logo to buy on board, in C.U.M's shop which is open from 22-01 both evenings. There will be men’s sizes from M-3XL and they cost SEK 300/EUR30. Black t-shirt with round neck. There are also Monday Bar Lanyards in different colours on sale for SEK50/EUR5. BRING CASH - YOU CAN FIND AN ATM MACHINE AT THE FERRY TERMINAL (but not on the ship) The merch is sold cash only, so don't forget to bring cash, preferably as even as possible. There is an ATM machine in the terminal, but not on the ship. Dress theme: WELCOME TO THE JUNGLE! There’s no limit to what some people will do with a dress theme. Or perhaps just dress in green with a some plants and birds.. And Dominika at C.U.M. is of course willing to help those of you who need some inspiration. LINEUP & SET TIMES Here’s the complete lineup and set times - with music styles. A good idea is to save this image on your phone! All times on the cruise are Estonian +1 hour, so forward your watch/phone 1 hour when boarding the ship, and keep it that way for the duration of the cruise. A good advice is to set the time setting on manual so the time doesn’t change when entering a different time zone. MONDAY BAR presents THE 2024 CRUISE (no 61) Friday-Sunday, September 20-22 (2 nights - 41h) M/S Baltic Queen Stockholm-Tallinn-Stockholm Cruise times Departure, Stockholm Tallink-Silja ferry terminal, Värtahamnen Friday, September 20, 17:30 (5:30 PM), local Swedish time Arrival, Tallinn Tallink D-terminal Saturday September 21, 10:45 (10:45 AM), local Estonian time (+1 hour) Departure, Tallinn Tallink D-terminal Saturday September 21, 18:00 (6 PM), local Estonian time (+1 hour) Arrival, Stockholm Tallink-Silja ferry terminal, Värtahamnen Sunday September 22, 10:30 (10:30 AM), local Swedish time Age limit: 18 years when boarding. Cabin prices starting at SEK 1690 per person. See u on the cruise! Monday Bar Crew 🥰 CRUISE HOMEPAGE  <https://www.mondaybar.com/home-monday-bar-presents-the-2024-cruise?ss_source=sscampaigns&ss_campaign_id=66e45797f43aea477de0643d&ss_email_id=66e462156e9778179559a8d8&ss_campaign_name=Newsletter%3A+Cruise+special+w.37+%F0%9F%9B%B3%EF%B8%8F&ss_campaign_sent_date=2024-09-13T16%3A14%3A13Z> FACEBOOK EVENT  <https://www.facebook.com/events/730815549006255>  <https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCBTe8_DMsFC3HYqEg4suMxg>  <http://facebook.com/mondaybar>  <http://instagram.com/mondaybar>  <http://twitter.com/mondaybar> © Monday Bar, 1992-2024 Högbergsgatan 18, SE-11620 Stockholm, Sweden Unsubscribe  <https://campaign-preferences.com/unsubscribe/RA3gdJg5WTVEfWGEDk2QfJYUD2rOh7rqvIsXFB31J1PoZsgP3sjXmlY-LvzpLjHyU3jV_c1ANgaK23VOCKnSoV3yDw1_dBjIol5V2gRExXZ2bgQWLXyOjQgxPM_t8L4oYIkVx3k-3ANACuoBwhcNB2A44TeJB2tdehZJxaQVMnxYGDi19bw43lb3RrFUyGiCXzX6gU_3RwVDlu9ndHp6NpD2ijT-5xLWmxe9GSPEg85m53X_z7qJwUtN80J2E527PU3I-GP0zHBXCpG8DdbQV8ZS_nAm2VzO67rQmJQdayKczKckmK17bfaitRN6LQff8PPZkY-jYeiT1ZOg90QBPSKQvFxFCyxIBjbb6gK16L2wLvj20QabU9s=>